{"key":"post-15582171","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>15582171</id>\n<content>With a reservoir, it's important not to fill it too often.&amp;nbsp; The cake must begin to dry out and lose moisture, and then you 'water' it to replace that moisture.&amp;nbsp; Avoid filling the reservoir every day because a waterlogged cake will perform as poorly as one which is too dry, but both will produce small, stunted fruits, often confusing the issue.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You can learn to judge water content by gently lifting each cake to feel for the weight.&amp;nbsp; If it's heavy, don't fill the reservoir or dunk.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>15582186</next>\n<prev>15582147</prev>\n<first>15581943</first>\n<last>15670193</last>\n<when>1325090674</when>\n<utime>12/28/11 06:44 PM</utime>\n</post>"}